(this name uses spanish naming customs: the first or paternal family name is gutiérrez and the second or maternal family name is gutiérrez.) esteban manuel gutiérrez gutiérrez (spanish pronunciation: [esˈteβan maˈnwel ɣuˈtjeres ɣuˈtjeres]; born 5 august 1991), is a mexican racing driver. from 2011 to 2014, gutiérrez drove for the sauber formula one team but lost his drive at the end of the 2014 season. he then signed with ferrari as their test and reserve driver for 2015. on 30 october 2015, gutiérrez was confirmed to drive for the new haas f1 team for the 2016 formula one season. in 2008, gutiérrez won the formula bmw europe championship title, becoming the youngest mexican driver to win an international championship at 17 years old. he also won the inaugural gp3 season in 2010. with the lotus gp team in 2012, he became the first gp3 graduate to finish in the top three of the gp2 parent series.